This analysis shows that the Colgate—Hell Creek flora is closely comparable with the flora 01 1116 type Lance and has a majority of species restricted elsewhere exclusively to beds of Lancian age. As a test case the analysis indicates perfect agreement between plants, vertebrates, marine invertebrates, and stratigraphy in the correlation of the Colgate—Hell Creek beds with those of the Lance formation at its type locality.
